1
00:00:21,155 --> 00:00:23,624
You could get sued for that.

2
00:00:25,893 --> 00:00:28,596
TOKYO DISTRICT COURT

3
00:00:53,154 --> 00:00:54,555
Sorry to keep you waiting.

4
00:00:55,756 --> 00:00:57,124
Nice to meet you.

5
00:00:57,725 --> 00:01:00,061
Are you Mr. Haneoka? I'm the paralegal--

6
00:01:00,127 --> 00:01:02,163
Ms. Shoko Ishida. I know.

7
00:01:03,230 --> 00:01:06,667
Thank you for taking on this case.
My father strained his back--

8
00:01:06,734 --> 00:01:08,169
I know that too.

9
00:01:08,969 --> 00:01:10,271
Do you always waste time?

10
00:01:11,939 --> 00:01:14,375
I've read the materials. Let's hurry.

11
00:01:17,978 --> 00:01:20,681
However, as a premise,

12
00:01:20,748 --> 00:01:25,319
she has no reason for a divorce
and wants to avoid divorce proceedings.

13
00:01:25,386 --> 00:01:27,721
Do you still not get it?

14
00:01:28,756 --> 00:01:33,360
They agreed to share the chores equally
because they're both working.

15
00:01:33,427 --> 00:01:37,031
But when they had a fight,
even though it was her duty,

16
00:01:37,098 --> 00:01:40,034
she intentionally excluded
the husband's laundry.

17
00:01:40,101 --> 00:01:43,504
I believe this is
a default of an obligation.

18
00:01:44,171 --> 00:01:47,842
She also banned him from smoking,
a habit of his since before marriage.

19
00:01:47,908 --> 00:01:53,681
And her unilateral decision to limit
his beer consumption to one 350 ml can

20
00:01:53,747 --> 00:01:58,619
were acts of moral harassment that caused
unbearable stress to my client.

21
00:02:00,988 --> 00:02:05,392
In addition, she gave her husband
only 400 yen for lunch,

22
00:02:05,459 --> 00:02:07,495
when she enjoyed course lunches herself.

23
00:02:07,561 --> 00:02:11,065
Such outrageous action has caused him
financial and emotional stress--

24
00:02:11,132 --> 00:02:12,933
No. Um…

25
00:02:13,534 --> 00:02:15,936
My wife can be sweet, too.

26
00:02:17,438 --> 00:02:18,606
Good work.

27
00:02:19,740 --> 00:02:21,442
Are you sure that went well?

28
00:02:21,509 --> 00:02:24,945
The client is only seeking
an amicable divorce. But you--

29
00:02:25,012 --> 00:02:27,481
By properly instilling
the wife's wrongdoings

30
00:02:27,548 --> 00:02:30,584
we're making the mediation committee
stand on the husband's side.

31
00:02:31,619 --> 00:02:32,987
May I say something?

32
00:02:34,188 --> 00:02:36,624
You may be a good lawyer,

33
00:02:36,690 --> 00:02:41,028
but in terms of lawyer ethics, I felt that
you made very dangerous statements.

34
00:02:41,095 --> 00:02:43,931
You could get sued by your client.

35
00:02:43,998 --> 00:02:46,500
I doubt we'll ever meet again,
but in the future--

36
00:02:46,567 --> 00:02:48,269
You're hard-headed, aren't you?

37
00:02:48,335 --> 00:02:49,403
Ms. Ishiko.

38
00:02:49,937 --> 00:02:50,604
Excuse me?

39
00:02:50,671 --> 00:02:54,575
Shoko Ishida. "Ishi" means "stone."
So, stone-headed Ishiko. Understood?

40
00:03:01,182 --> 00:03:02,850
<i>Sono contento.</i>

41
00:03:02,917 --> 00:03:04,618
By the way, about your attitude.

42
00:03:04,685 --> 00:03:07,221
Aren't you being rude
to your future partner?

43
00:03:07,755 --> 00:03:08,756
What?

44
00:03:08,822 --> 00:03:11,425
I'm officially hired starting next week.

45
00:03:13,227 --> 00:03:15,095
<i>Dad, please explain!</i>

46
00:03:15,162 --> 00:03:18,766
Your voice is hurting my back. Ouch.

47
00:03:18,832 --> 00:03:21,202
I thought you hired him just for the day.

48
00:03:21,268 --> 00:03:25,206
<i>Well, I'm getting old.</i>
<i>I thought I should hire someone new.</i>

49
00:03:25,272 --> 00:03:27,208
Someone like him?!

50
00:03:27,274 --> 00:03:29,176
But it's already been decided.

51
00:03:29,243 --> 00:03:31,045
He's on our website too.

52
00:03:31,111 --> 00:03:33,080
<i>-Ow, ow.</i>
-What?

53
00:03:35,883 --> 00:03:38,052
LAWYER YOSHIO HANEOKA

54
00:03:40,621 --> 00:03:42,089
"Call me Haneo."

55
00:03:42,590 --> 00:03:47,394
"I want to be a free man,
who can fly anywhere like a feather."

56
00:03:49,663 --> 00:03:50,631
What's with him?

57
00:04:09,450 --> 00:04:11,252
TOWN OF BIG PORTIONS KAMOGAYA

58
00:04:21,996 --> 00:04:24,598
THREE DAYS LATER

59
00:04:27,134 --> 00:04:28,068
Alright.

60
00:04:35,709 --> 00:04:36,543
Okay.

61
00:04:38,812 --> 00:04:39,813
USHIO

62
00:04:42,049 --> 00:04:48,188
Our motto is "Be an umbrella
to protect those who live earnestly."

63
00:04:48,255 --> 00:04:51,191
Whatever the request may be,

64
00:04:51,258 --> 00:04:52,693
there's an important…

65
00:04:52,760 --> 00:04:54,094
Please take it easy.

66
00:04:54,161 --> 00:04:54,995
Oh, really?

67
00:04:55,062 --> 00:04:56,697
Then I guess I will.

68
00:04:57,231 --> 00:04:59,667
BE AN UMBRELLA
TO PROTECT THOSE WHO LIVE EARNESTLY.

69
00:05:01,502 --> 00:05:03,270
It's more spacious than I thought.

70
00:05:03,337 --> 00:05:04,838
<i>Sono contento.</i>

71
00:05:06,373 --> 00:05:09,476
Oh, can I see the materials
I returned the other day?

72
00:05:09,543 --> 00:05:10,377
Sure.

73
00:05:11,979 --> 00:05:14,615
I thought I'd take a look
from a different angle.

74
00:05:20,754 --> 00:05:22,823
"A charismatic phrase."

75
00:05:22,890 --> 00:05:25,426
"Maybe I should
mutter something in Italian."

76
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:27,561
This was in the file.

77
00:05:28,462 --> 00:05:30,698
"Neglecting husband's laundry is
default of obligation."

78
00:05:30,764 --> 00:05:34,134
"Banning smoking is moral harassment."
I found these too.

79
00:05:34,702 --> 00:05:39,773
You accidentally slipped these help notes
and were desperate to get them back.

80
00:05:39,840 --> 00:05:40,607
Am I wrong?

81
00:05:42,309 --> 00:05:45,346
Could you be acting out
the unconventional great lawyers

82
00:05:45,412 --> 00:05:47,948
that we see on TV shows and novels?

83
00:05:48,015 --> 00:05:50,951
Reading my notes without permission
is a breach of privacy.

84
00:05:51,018 --> 00:05:53,020
It wasn't on purpose.

85
00:05:53,087 --> 00:05:55,522
-Even so--
-Hang on! It's still my turn.

86
00:05:55,589 --> 00:05:56,323
What?

87
00:05:56,390 --> 00:05:58,525
Now, I'm guessing that was on purpose too.

88
00:05:58,592 --> 00:05:59,426
That?

89
00:05:59,493 --> 00:06:01,762
That, when you appeared just in time.

90
00:06:01,829 --> 00:06:03,731
I knew something was weird.

91
00:06:03,797 --> 00:06:07,234
I looked away because you weren't there,
but I heard a voice.

92
00:06:07,301 --> 00:06:09,403
And the next thing I know, you were there.

93
00:06:09,470 --> 00:06:11,605
You showed up in such a short time.

94
00:06:11,672 --> 00:06:15,943
<i>Weren't you just hiding behind the pillar</i>
<i>to appear at the right time?</i>

95
00:06:16,443 --> 00:06:17,778
Sorry to keep you waiting.

96
00:06:18,779 --> 00:06:19,880
And…

97
00:06:19,947 --> 00:06:22,316
that "<i>sono contento</i>" you keep saying.

98
00:06:23,217 --> 00:06:25,185
Apparently, it means "satisfied."

99
00:06:25,252 --> 00:06:27,454
But it doesn't make sense at all.

100
00:06:28,255 --> 00:06:29,356
<i>Sono contento.</i>

101
00:06:30,324 --> 00:06:33,026
I'm sorry, but it's just lame.
It's no Sonokong.

102
00:06:33,093 --> 00:06:35,829
Who cares?
There are tons of lawyers today.

103
00:06:35,896 --> 00:06:39,733
It's saturated. So we need to show people
what kind of lawyer we are.

104
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:44,004
There's cosplay lawyers and idol lawyers.
I just happen to be a genius lawyer.

105
00:06:45,739 --> 00:06:47,941
-I see.
-It's called branding.

106
00:06:48,008 --> 00:06:50,244
I figured we'd get more requests that way.

107
00:06:50,310 --> 00:06:52,346
I'm happy to receive more requests.

108
00:06:52,413 --> 00:06:54,982
But your actions and words
could get us in trouble.

109
00:06:55,048 --> 00:06:59,119
We're a small firm.
One scandal could put us out of business.

110
00:06:59,186 --> 00:07:01,622
Please stop that behavior right now.

111
00:07:02,556 --> 00:07:03,457
-No.
-Stop it.

112
00:07:03,524 --> 00:07:04,525
No.

113
00:07:04,591 --> 00:07:06,860
Your fake talent
will be exposed in no time.

114
00:07:06,927 --> 00:07:09,229
I don't want to hear that
from a paralegal!

115
00:07:09,863 --> 00:07:12,433
From you, who still can't be a lawyer.

116
00:07:14,668 --> 00:07:18,839
It's not that I can't be a lawyer.
I choose not to be one.

117
00:07:19,339 --> 00:07:20,174
Huh?

118
00:07:20,908 --> 00:07:25,312
To be honest, I don't think
my legal abilities are inferior to yours.

119
00:07:25,379 --> 00:07:27,114
Yeah, right. That's not true.

120
00:07:28,148 --> 00:07:29,516
That's so lame.

121
00:07:33,654 --> 00:07:37,624
As a paralegal,
I will assist you perfectly.

122
00:07:37,691 --> 00:07:38,892
Oh?

123
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:48,335
Hello, this is Ushio Law Firm.

124
00:07:48,869 --> 00:07:52,272
<i>I would like to request</i>
<i>Mr. Haneoka to look at my case.</i>

125
00:07:52,339 --> 00:07:53,173
What?

126
00:07:55,209 --> 00:07:56,577
See?

127
00:08:05,752 --> 00:08:07,821
Oh, right. I see.

128
00:08:07,888 --> 00:08:10,157
So, you saw me on the website.

129
00:08:10,791 --> 00:08:11,758
Yes.

130
00:08:15,629 --> 00:08:18,131
I will make sure
you will be <i>sono contento</i>.

131
00:08:19,032 --> 00:08:20,033
"Sono"?

132
00:08:20,100 --> 00:08:21,368
Please have a seat.

133
00:08:23,136 --> 00:08:24,004
Here.

134
00:08:24,071 --> 00:08:25,672
-He saw the website.
-Thanks.

135
00:08:26,240 --> 00:08:29,042
And he thought I was the one.

136
00:08:30,944 --> 00:08:34,214
And what is your request?

137
00:08:36,016 --> 00:08:37,284
The thing is…

138
00:08:39,653 --> 00:08:41,822
I was charging my phone in a café

139
00:08:43,190 --> 00:08:44,424
and I got sued for that.

140
00:08:46,159 --> 00:08:48,362
Okay, let me confirm.

141
00:08:51,532 --> 00:08:55,969
Mr. Oba, you've been frequently going to
Café de Sevon for the past month,

142
00:08:56,036 --> 00:08:58,505
where you stay from 7 to 9:30 p.m.

143
00:08:58,572 --> 00:09:01,542
and used their outlet
to charge your phone.

144
00:09:01,608 --> 00:09:03,644
-I didn't use that much.
-It's a bother.

145
00:09:03,710 --> 00:09:06,113
<i>In response, the café manager suddenly</i>

146
00:09:06,179 --> 00:09:09,583
<i>demanded one million yen</i>
<i>for emotional distress</i>

147
00:09:09,650 --> 00:09:12,920
<i>on top of the electricity bill.</i>

148
00:09:13,487 --> 00:09:14,321
Is that correct?

149
00:09:16,523 --> 00:09:19,593
If I ignore him, he said he'll… You know.

150
00:09:20,360 --> 00:09:21,428
No, I don't know.

151
00:09:21,495 --> 00:09:23,664
-He'll file civil and criminal lawsuits.
-Oh, civil…

152
00:09:24,631 --> 00:09:27,067
How can he sue me for something like this?

153
00:09:27,134 --> 00:09:28,635
This isn't America.

154
00:09:28,702 --> 00:09:31,004
How often do you go to this café?

155
00:09:31,071 --> 00:09:31,872
Almost every day.

156
00:09:31,939 --> 00:09:33,173
That often?

157
00:09:34,641 --> 00:09:37,611
I only have Wednesdays off
and I work the rest of the week.

158
00:09:38,278 --> 00:09:42,349
So I stop by every day after work
to do some small tasks.

159
00:09:43,450 --> 00:09:44,785
Why this café?

160
00:09:45,619 --> 00:09:46,887
It's cozy.

161
00:09:50,190 --> 00:09:51,592
And you work at--

162
00:09:51,658 --> 00:09:53,560
Car Captain. A used car dealership!

163
00:09:53,627 --> 00:09:54,661
Right. Okay.

164
00:09:56,029 --> 00:09:59,333
What do you think?
A million yen is just too…

165
00:10:00,233 --> 00:10:01,568
Um, first of all,

166
00:10:02,502 --> 00:10:04,705
um, can you see me?

167
00:10:04,771 --> 00:10:07,674
First of all, this is a warning letter.

168
00:10:08,442 --> 00:10:10,911
You haven't been sued.

169
00:10:10,978 --> 00:10:11,645
Oh.

170
00:10:12,145 --> 00:10:14,615
<i>However,</i>
<i>Article 245 of the Penal Code states that</i>

171
00:10:14,681 --> 00:10:17,150
<i>"electricity is considered a property."</i>

172
00:10:17,217 --> 00:10:19,553
Using the outlet
without permission is a theft--

173
00:10:19,620 --> 00:10:20,520
Th-Theft?

174
00:10:20,587 --> 00:10:25,258
Also, if it becomes a criminal case,
the police will question and arrest you--

175
00:10:25,325 --> 00:10:26,526
A-Arrest?!

176
00:10:26,593 --> 00:10:29,129
-Let's calm down for a moment.
-I'll be arrested?

177
00:10:30,030 --> 00:10:32,265
-I'm sorry.
-Let's take a deep breath.

178
00:10:32,332 --> 00:10:34,101
And breathe out.

179
00:10:39,473 --> 00:10:41,074
-Good.
-Thank you.

180
00:10:41,708 --> 00:10:44,111
I'm really sorry for what I did.

181
00:10:44,778 --> 00:10:47,814
But can we somehow settle for 100,000 yen?

182
00:10:48,382 --> 00:10:49,249
Okay.

183
00:10:49,883 --> 00:10:51,451
Well, a million yen is a rip-off.

184
00:10:51,518 --> 00:10:54,121
By the way,
our initial consultation is free.

185
00:10:54,187 --> 00:10:58,258
The retainer fee is 100,000 yen
plus a contingency fee. Is that alright?

186
00:10:58,325 --> 00:10:59,226
Yes.

187
00:10:59,292 --> 00:11:01,828
Then your signature here please.

188
00:11:09,636 --> 00:11:11,304
Why are you following me?

189
00:11:11,371 --> 00:11:13,106
You could cause trouble for us.

190
00:11:13,173 --> 00:11:15,642
Don't worry. This is an easy case.

191
00:11:15,709 --> 00:11:19,479
There are cases where small claims
were made into criminal charges.

192
00:11:19,546 --> 00:11:23,984
In 2008, a teenager was arrested for
charging her phone at a train station.

193
00:11:24,051 --> 00:11:28,555
In 2010, a man who pulled electricity from
a shared outlet was sentenced for--

194
00:11:28,622 --> 00:11:29,756
It'll be fine.

195
00:11:30,424 --> 00:11:32,659
He'll back off if a lawyer shows up.

196
00:11:43,170 --> 00:11:48,942
We believe that this claim for damages is
clearly an overcharge.

197
00:11:51,078 --> 00:11:51,912
And?

198
00:11:52,479 --> 00:11:53,246
Huh?

199
00:11:53,814 --> 00:11:54,781
It's too complicated.

200
00:11:56,550 --> 00:11:57,718
Well, as I said…

201
00:11:57,784 --> 00:12:00,287
You're saying you can't comply, right?

202
00:12:00,353 --> 00:12:02,789
It's not that we can't comply.
Not everything…

203
00:12:02,856 --> 00:12:06,727
He stays for hours every day
and even charges his phone. It's annoying.

204
00:12:06,793 --> 00:12:07,894
<i>Right.</i>

205
00:12:10,163 --> 00:12:12,199
<i>Have you warned him several times?</i>

206
00:12:12,265 --> 00:12:13,100
<i>No.</i>

207
00:12:13,667 --> 00:12:14,334
Then…

208
00:12:14,401 --> 00:12:16,203
There's a written warning.

209
00:12:16,269 --> 00:12:17,871
PLEASE DO NOT CHARGE

210
00:12:17,938 --> 00:12:19,473
That's not really…

211
00:12:19,539 --> 00:12:21,108
Are you saying I'm at fault?

212
00:12:21,174 --> 00:12:22,175
No, I meant--

213
00:12:22,242 --> 00:12:26,179
It may not be much, but it becomes a
pretty big damage if everyone does it.

214
00:12:26,246 --> 00:12:27,914
Do you know how stressful it is?

215
00:12:28,415 --> 00:12:32,185
It's a million yen for many reasons.
Also as a warning to other customers.

216
00:12:32,252 --> 00:12:33,420
This is not negotiable.

217
00:12:33,987 --> 00:12:36,189
Could you reduce the amount?
It's clearly--

218
00:12:36,256 --> 00:12:39,559
Then let's just let the police
or the court handle it.

219
00:12:39,626 --> 00:12:41,928
We're getting nowhere bickering here.

220
00:12:41,995 --> 00:12:42,829
Um…

221
00:13:09,556 --> 00:13:12,826
What's wrong? You suddenly went quiet.

222
00:13:14,261 --> 00:13:15,262
It's no good.

223
00:13:15,962 --> 00:13:16,830
Huh?

224
00:13:16,897 --> 00:13:18,532
That manager won't back down.

225
00:13:19,366 --> 00:13:21,234
And he seems to have financial trouble.

226
00:13:21,301 --> 00:13:22,068
What?

227
00:13:22,135 --> 00:13:24,538
<i>The prices of the drinks</i>
<i>were raised by 50 yen</i>

228
00:13:24,604 --> 00:13:26,807
<i>and 130 yen for pizza toast in a year.</i>

229
00:13:26,873 --> 00:13:27,941
You went there often?

230
00:13:28,008 --> 00:13:29,509
No, just once.

231
00:13:29,576 --> 00:13:31,745
Come on, pretending to be a genius--

232
00:13:31,812 --> 00:13:33,880
Let's persuade our client. Okay?

233
00:13:34,447 --> 00:13:36,650
If he can't pay,
we should give up on settling.

234
00:13:37,484 --> 00:13:38,485
Excuse me?

235
00:13:40,620 --> 00:13:41,454
I'm giving up.

236
00:13:42,455 --> 00:13:43,290
What?

237
00:13:45,025 --> 00:13:47,194
You're giving up way too early.

238
00:13:48,228 --> 00:13:50,730
If we can't settle,
there'll be no contingency fee.

239
00:13:50,797 --> 00:13:52,666
You negotiate with the manager then.

240
00:13:52,732 --> 00:13:56,002
You know that paralegals can't
negotiate legally, don't you?

241
00:13:56,069 --> 00:13:58,972
Besides, I believe my role is to
stay behind the scene

242
00:13:59,039 --> 00:14:02,075
and assist the lawyers to do a good job.

243
00:14:02,676 --> 00:14:05,512
It's against my rule to
ignore you and stand out.

244
00:14:05,579 --> 00:14:07,547
I don't care about your rule.

245
00:14:07,614 --> 00:14:09,082
Mr. Haneoka!

246
00:14:11,184 --> 00:14:12,085
Huh?

247
00:14:13,053 --> 00:14:14,354
What's his problem?

248
00:14:26,900 --> 00:14:29,302
Hey, Shoko. Shoko?

249
00:14:30,403 --> 00:14:32,873
Could you raise my allowance--

250
00:14:32,939 --> 00:14:33,573
No.

251
00:14:35,609 --> 00:14:36,576
Okay.

252
00:14:46,119 --> 00:14:47,554
This month is tight again.

253
00:14:55,095 --> 00:14:56,897
ENGAGEMENT LETTER

254
00:14:59,132 --> 00:15:01,201
CONTINGENCY FEE

255
00:15:22,622 --> 00:15:24,624
Hey, Oba. Make sure to empty the trash.

256
00:15:24,691 --> 00:15:25,725
Yes.

257
00:15:54,020 --> 00:15:56,523
